## Documentation Rules

### File Structure
- Main project overview: [README.md](mdc:README.md)
- Implementation guide: [IMPLEMENTATION.md](mdc:IMPLEMENTATION.md)
- Database schema: [DATABASE.md](mdc:DATABASE.md)
- Crawler implementation: [CRAWLER.md](mdc:CRAWLER.md)
- Master data queries: [MASTER_DATA.md](mdc:MASTER_DATA.md)
- Project TODOs: [TODO.md](mdc:TODO.md)

### Documentation Standards
- Use Korean for all documentation.
- Keep documentation concise and implementation-focused.
- Include code examples where appropriate.
- Use proper Markdown formatting.
- Reference other files using `[filename](mdc:filename)` format.

### Code Documentation
- Include docstrings for all functions and classes.
- Use type hints for better code understanding.
- Document all environment variables.
- Include usage examples in code comments.

### API Documentation
- Document all API endpoints with examples.
- Include request/response schemas.
- Document error codes and messages.
- Provide usage examples for each endpoint.

### Database Documentation
- Document all table schemas and relationships.
- Include sample queries and usage patterns.
- Document indexes and constraints.
- Explain data flow and relationships.